item.description:
TL;DR The Docker BuildKit buildx CLI plugin simplifies building Docker images for different OS/CPU platforms (e.g. linux/amd64, linux/arm64, linux/arm, windows/amd64)
So why is it a big deal now? Who needs Docker images for Arm platform anyway. Raspberry Pi geeks?
A good reason for this is just a one word Graviton2&hellip;
